\binom{2014}{1} &= 2014 \\
\binom{2014}{2} &= 2014 \cdot \frac{2013}{2} \\
&\vdots \\
\binom{2014}{62} &= \binom{2014}{62}
\end{align*}

We can see that $\binom{2014}{k} = \binom{2014}{2014-k}$, so we can pair up the terms in $S$ and simplify:

\begin{align*}
S &= \sum \limits_{k=0}^{62} \dbinom{2014}{k} \\
&= \binom{2014}{0} + \binom{2014}{1} + \binom{2014}{2} + \cdots + \binom{2014}{62} \\
&= \binom{2014}{0} + \binom{2014}{1} + \binom{2014}{2} + \cdots + \binom{2014}{62} \\
&= 1 + 2014 + \binom{2014}{2} + \cdots + \binom{2014}{62} \\
&= 1 + 2014 + 2014 \cdot \frac{2013}{2} + \cdots + \binom{2014}{62} \\
&= 1 + 2014 + 2014 \cdot \frac{2013}{2} + \cdots + \binom{2014}{62} \\
&= 1 + 2014 + 2014 \cdot \frac{2013}{2} + \cdots + \binom{2014}{62}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the remainder when $S$ is divided by $2017$ is $\boxed{1}$.

